com.vividsolutions.jcs.algorithm.linearreference
Class LengthIndexedLine

java.lang.Object
  com.vividsolutions.jcs.algorithm.linearreference.LengthIndexedLine
public class LengthIndexedLine
extends java.lang.Object

Supports linear referencing along a LineString using the length along the line as the index.

indexOf

public double indexOf(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate pt)
Computes the index for a point on the line. (The point does not necessarily have to lie precisely on the line, but if it is far from the line the accuracy and performance of this function is not guaranteed. Use project(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate) to compute a guaranteed result for points known to not be on the line).

Parameters:
pt - a point on the line
Returns:
the index of the point
See Also:
project

indicesOf

public double[] indicesOf(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.LineString subLine)
Computes the indices for a subline of the line. (The subline must conform to the line; that is, all vertices in the subline (except possibly the first and last) must be vertices of the line and occcur in the same order).

Parameters:
subLine - a subLine of the line
Returns:
a pair of indices for the start and end of the subline.

project

public double project(com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate pt)
Computes the index for the closest point on the line to the given point. If more than one point has the closest distance the first one along the line is returned. (The point does not necessarily have to lie precisely on the line.)

Parameters:
pt - a point on the line
Returns:
the index of the point
